  "text": "Glycosaminoglycan extraction from cryoprecipitate and Cohn-Oncley fractions Cryoprecipitate and fraction I, fraction IIþIII, fraction IV-1, fraction IV-4, and fraction V were suspended in 0.05 mol/l Tris-HCl, pH 7.4, and were treated with proteases added sequentially as follows: papain, trypsin, chimotrypsin, collagenase and pepsin [CITATION_1] . After proteolysis, the sample was centrifuged at 15 000 Â g for 10 min, and the supernatant was treated with ethanol to precipitate glycosaminoglycans [CITATION_2] . The precipitate was resuspended in distilled water, dialysed against distilled water, and lyophilized. The retentate was dissolved in distilled water and stored at -80 until use.",
